<br>
- Dain: <br>
Dain is, at least on our server, up quite oftenly. Now, Dain's loot table, from my perspective is complete and utter trash for the most part. The Hammer is a fun solo toy, but nothing beyond that. His loot it garbage for me, except one piece. The problem is, his head which drops 100% of the time, is used to make arguably the best warrior/melee belt in the game. Short of perhaps Girdle of Thorns for warriors (which is actually worse than dain's belt after casting the effect), Belt of Dwarf Slaying is the best belt in the game for melee classes and some casters as well. <br>
<br>
- Yelinak:<br>
Same case as above. HOwever, his head is also used to make 75hp/75 mana 41% haste gloves, good for both melee and caster classes once again. He also drops a talisman used to make an ST key. <br>
<br>
- Tormax:<br>
This I fear is the worst mob of them all. Tormax wields one of the best loot tables I've seen in the game, better than every other velious mob except AoW from my perspective; and even better than quite a few luclin mobs. <br>
a ) Boots of the Storm are the 3rd best plate melee boots in the game. <br>
b) His head is used to make 85hp/110 mana boots with FT-2. Very few casters I've met have better<br>
c) His crown is a 100hp item with saves to all and 35ac. The crown is also an all/all item with only 1.0 weight; a perfect item for many classes<br>
d) His head can also be used to make a 100hp all/all droppable helm.<br>
e) 75mana ring (I think 75hp on it as well)<br>
f) ST key. <br>
<br>
The loot table above shows why Tormax would be so popular<br>
<br>
- NToV:<br>
For the most part, the drops are not very good. However, Blackstar, Cloak of Thorns, Wyvern-hide greaves, are a couple of the very attractive items that drop in this zone. They are once again mixed in with some other poor drops.<br>
<br>
- AoW:<br>
His loot table is awesome (for me at least). True, some of the ubers have no more use for a BoC, or War bow of rallos or monk greaves. However, they have uses for the rare helm or rallos zek, and BELIEVE me, they all have use for the Ring of Destruction. <br>
<br>
<br>
The reason you are seeing this pattern going on is because certain amazing items have been placed on the loot table of easy, lower-tier mobs. The loot is heavily sought, and make these mobs attractive to higher-end guilds. The fact that more guilds go for them makes them all the more competitive. The guilds go for 1 or 2 items and sell the rest. after all, cash is somethng all uber guilds could use considering the necessity for lots of peridots and the like. <br>
<br>
It's not very fair; but this is unfortunately how these things work. <p><center><p><font size = 3 colo = "blue"><b>Wilhelmm D'Averam<br>Warlord of the Apocalypse</b></font></p></center>

